The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 March is 227,738 (26,248.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 February, there were 4,296 new confirmed cases (495.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 February, there were 6,146 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (1,850 fewer cases).
